</body>
</html>

📄 File 2: Dockerfile
dockerfile# Use official Nginx image as base
FROM nginx:latest

# Remove default nginx page
RUN rm -rf /usr/share/nginx/html/*

# Copy our website files to nginx folder
COPY index.html /usr/share/nginx/html/index.html

# Expose port 80
EXPOSE 80

# Start nginx
CMD ["nginx", "-g", "daemon off;"]

🖥️ Steps to Run
Step 1: Install Docker
Download from:
https://www.docker.com/products/docker-desktop/

Download Docker Desktop for Windows
Double click installer → Next → Install → Finish
Restart your laptop

Step 2: Verify Docker is Installed
bashdocker --version
✅ Should show:
Docker version 24.x.x
Step 3: Create Project Folder
bashmkdir docker-website
cd docker-website
notepad index.html
notepad Dockerfile
Paste respective code and save each file.
Step 4: Build Docker Image
bashdocker build -t my-static-website .
✅ Should show:
Successfully built xxxxxxxx
Successfully tagged my-static-website:latest
Step 5: Run the Container
bashdocker run -d -p 8080:80 --name my-website my-static-website


If Docker Desktop Won't Open:
Check if Virtualization is enabled:

Press Ctrl + Shift + Esc → Task Manager
Click Performance tab
Click CPU
Check Virtualization: Enabled ✅

